<img class=" wp-image-1318352" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Roof-560x417.jpg?w=560&#038;ssl=1" alt="" style="margin:10px auto;max-width:560px;max-width:100%" data-recalc-dims="1"> For allegedly stealing roofing sheet belonging to a church, a 22-year-old man, Wakili Ganiyu has been sentenced to eight months in correctional custody. The charge read in the court disclosed that the defendant stole the iron sheet valued N80,000 belonging to Dream Centre of Life Oasis International Church. It added that the defendant conspired with a 17 years old suspect to commit the alleged offence. The police prosecutor, inspector Olayiwola Rasaq told the court that the accused person committed the offence on January 5, 2020, at about 9:30 pm at Osunjela area of the state. He added that the accused person was caught by one Godwin Adu, a night guard in the church. According to him, the offence committed contravenes and is punishable under section 516 and section 390 cap 34 vol ll law of Osun state 2002. The accused person pleaded guilty to the two counts levelled against him by the police. The Magistrate, Opeyemi Badmus found the defendant guilty but transferred the underage case to the family court. He then sentenced the Wakili to eight months imprisonment. Vanguard News Nigeria. The post Man bags 8 months for stealing church’s roofing sheet in Osun appeared first on Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard Osogbo – A young woman, Nofisat Raji, 35 years old, has been sentenced to six months imprisonment by an Osogbo Magistrate Court for allegedly stealing a sum of N14,500. The police prosecutor, Inspector Oladoye Joshua had told the court that the accused person committed the offences at Fayemi street, Osogbo at… September 20, 2017 In "News" A 20-year old man, identified as Adedeji Olalekan was, on Thursday arraigned before an Osogbo Magistrate court in Osun for the alleged theft of one Toyota Corolla, 2003 model, belonging to a legal practitioner. Polic